A vintage 1970s-style illustration of a rotary telephone melting and morphing into a sleek modern cordless handset, set against a warm amber and burnt orange gradient background. The transformation happens mid-frame with liquid-like drips and swirls connecting the old and new devices. Tangled copper wires from the old phone gradually become clean fiber optic cables glowing with soft blue light toward the modern side. The scene sits on a mid-century modern wooden desk with a frustrated person's hands visible at the frame edges, palms up in exasperation. Muted teal, mustard yellow, and cream color palette with subtle halftone dot texture throughout, reminiscent of vintage magazine advertisements.
